Q1. WAP to take check if the triangle is valid or not. If the validity is established, do check if the triangle is isosceles, equilateral, right angle, or scalene. Take sides of the triangle 
as input from a user.
Solution:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    float a, b, c;

    printf("Enter side a: ");
    scanf("%f", &a);

    printf("Enter side b: ");
    scanf("%f", &b);

    printf("Enter side c: ");
    scanf("%f", &c);

    if (a + b > c && a + c > b && b + c > a) {
        printf("The triangle is valid.\n");

        if (a == b && b == c) {
            printf("It is an Equilateral Triangle.\n");
        }
        else if (a == b || b == c || a == c) {
            printf("It is an Isosceles Triangle.\n");
        }
        else {
            printf("It is a Scalene Triangle.\n");
        }

        if ( (a*a == b*b + c*c) ||
             (b*b == a*a + c*c) ||
             (c*c == a*a + b*b) ) {
            printf("It is also a Right-Angled Triangle.\n");
        }
    }
    else {
        printf("The triangle is NOT valid.\n");
    }

    return 0;
}

Q2. WAP to compute the BMI Index of the person and print the BMI values as per the following ranges. You can use the following formula to compute BMI= weight(kgs)/Height(Mts)*Height(Mts)
Starvation        -   <15
Anorexic          -   15.1 to 17.5
Underweight       -   17.6 to 18.5
Ideal             -   18.6 to 24.9
Overweight        -   25 to 25.9
Obese             -   30 to 39.9
Morbidity Obese   -   40.0 above
Solution:
